apiDescription: Asserts that two expressions are not equal to each other.
On panic, this macro will print the values of the expressions with their debug representations.

Unlike assert_ne!, debug_assert_ne! statements are only enabled in non optimized builds by default. An optimized build will omit all debug_assert_ne! statements unless -C debug-assertions is passed to the compiler. This makes debug_assert_ne! useful for checks that are too expensive to be present in a release build but may be helpful during development.
